
All helper methods return **native Python dict / list** structures already
decoded from JSON. If you need the raw `requests.Response` object you can
access `client.session` directly.

## 4. Error handling

| Exception                              | When it happens                                       |
| -------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| `requests.HTTPError`                   | Non-2×× status code from the server                   |
| `FileNotFoundError`                    | `/track` or `/segments` endpoint not available        |
| `ValueError`                           | Mandatory parameter missing (e.g. neither query nor where) |

The examples catch the above and print a friendly message.
